    "dateModified": "2026-06-13","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/online-scrabble-etiquette"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the basic etiquette rules for online Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Key etiquette rules include: play at a reasonable pace (do not stall), do not abandon games you are losing, be gracious in both victory and defeat, avoid using external word tools during rated games, do not trash-talk in chat, resign rather than letting your clock expire if you must leave, and say good game at the end of each match."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is it rude to play slowly in online Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In timed games, using your full allotted time is acceptable — that is what the clock is for. In untimed or turn-based games, taking more than 24 hours per move without explanation is generally considered inconsiderate. If you need extra time, a brief message explaining the delay shows respect for your opponent's time."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Should I resign if I am losing badly in online Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"This depends on context. In casual games, resignation is acceptable when the outcome is certain. In rated games, many players prefer to play to the end because spread (point difference) affects standings. A good guideline: if you are down by more than 150 points with fewer than 5 tiles in the bag, resignation is reasonable. Always resign gracefully rather than abandoning."}}]})} />
